author: National Geographic
description:
How do you treat a suspected case of bewitchment? With a witch bottle, of course. These anti-bewitchment devices were bottles filled with urine and small objects like hair, coins, and pins, before being buried in an attempt to fend off illness and misfortune caused by unknown malign forces. Learn more about their history: https://on.natgeo.com/3KJLnRE
